         <abstract id="aspace_df87502d09ce7fb676a3ed093895d9a2">Writings by and about Colenso document the controversies that surrounded this church leader in South Africa. John William Colenso (1814-1883) was appointed Bishop of Natal, South Africa in 1854. He was a controversial figure due to his stance on polygamy and his theology.</abstract>
